Full Monitoring Flow in EKS (Hinglish)
Pods run ho rahe hain cluster me
Ye jo app ya services chal rahi hain, unke internal state aur metrics chahiye monitoring ke liye.
Example: CPU usage, memory, pod status, deployments etc.
kube-state-metrics / Metrics Exporter
Ye ek pod + service create karta hai.
Ye pod cluster state ka data /metrics endpoint pe expose karta hai.

Example URL:

http://kube-state-metrics:8080/metrics
Service
Ye kube-state-metrics pod ko cluster ke andar access karne ke liye address deta hai.
Service ek stable IP / DNS provide karta hai, chahe pod restart ho jaye.
ServiceMonitor (Important)
Ye Prometheus ko batata hai ki kaunsi service ko scrape karna hai aur kitni frequency me.

Example:

matchLabels:
  app: kube-state-metrics
interval: 30s
Matlab: /metrics endpoint ko har 30 second me scrape karo.
Prometheus Operator
Ye cluster me run hota hai aur ServiceMonitor objects ko watch karta hai.
Automatically Prometheus ka config update karta hai.
Aapko manually prometheus.yml edit nahi karna padta.
Prometheus
Operator ke through Prometheus ko pata chal gaya ki kya scrape karna hai.
Prometheus /metrics call karta hai aur data store kar leta hai.
Example: Pod CPU usage, memory usage, pod count, restarts etc.
Alerting (Prometheus Alertmanager)
Prometheus rules ke through thresholds set karte hain.
Example: CPU > 80%, Pod down, Memory > 70%
Agar condition meet hoti hai, Alertmanager notification send karta hai:
Slack, Email, Teams, SMS, Webhook
Visualization (Optional)
Prometheus se data ko Grafana me visualize kar sakte ho.
Dashboards me graphs, trends, history, alerts etc.
One-line Full Flow (Hinglish)
Pods → kube-state-metrics → Service → ServiceMonitor → Prometheus Operator → Prometheus → AlertManager → Metrics/Alerts

💡 Real-life analogy (easy):

Pods = Students working
kube-state-metrics = Teacher giving test scores
Service = Classroom address
ServiceMonitor = Timetable (when to collect data)
Prometheus Operator = Coordinator telling student where to go
Prometheus = Student collecting notes
AlertManager = Parent/Principal gets alerted if something is wrong




